

# 🌳 Right Side View of Binary Tree (BFS)

## 🧠 Concept

* We need to see the tree from the **right side**
* At every level, only **one node is visible**
* That node is the **rightmost node of that level**

👉 Core idea:

> “For each level, take the last node”

---

## ⚙️ Approach (Your BFS with Level Marker)

### 💡 Idea

* Use **level order traversal (BFS)**
* Use `null` to mark **end of each level**
* Track last node of each level using `prev`

---

### 🔁 Flow

1. Add root to queue
2. Add `null` → marks end of level
3. Traverse queue:

   * If node is **not null**:

     * Store value in `prev`
     * Add children to queue
   * If node is **null**:

     * Add `prev` to result (last node of level)
     * Add another `null` (if queue not empty)

---

## 💻 Code 

```java
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> rightSideView(TreeNode root) {
        // Edge case: empty tree
        if (root == null) {
            return new ArrayList<>();
        }

        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
        Queue<TreeNode> q = new LinkedList<>();

        q.add(root);
        q.add(null); // marks end of level

        int prev = -1; // stores last node of level

        while (!q.isEmpty()) {
            TreeNode curr = q.remove();

            if (curr == null) {
                // end of current level
                if (q.isEmpty()) {
                    list.add(prev); // last level
                    return list;
                }

                list.add(prev); // add rightmost node
                q.add(null);    // mark next level

            } else {
                prev = curr.val; // keep updating → last node of level

                if (curr.left != null) {
                    q.add(curr.left);
                }
                if (curr.right != null) {
                    q.add(curr.right);
                }
            }
        }
        return list;
    }
}
```

---

## 🔍 Key Points

* `prev` always stores **last node seen in current level**
* `null` helps detect **level boundary**
* When `null` is reached → level completed
* Add `prev` → gives **rightmost node**

---

## ⚠️ Learnings / Improvements

* Using `null` marker works but is **not optimal**
* Cleaner approach exists using:

  * `queue.size()` (preferred in interviews)
* `prev = -1` is not ideal (what if tree contains -1?)

---

